      • parseNumber

        public static double parseNumber(java.lang.String s)
                          throws java.lang.Exception
        Turn a notation number string into a real number. If this notation doesn't contain "e", then it's not a scientific notation. If it's not a scientific notation number, turn it into real number directly, else call parseScientific method to parse scientific notation.
        参数:
        s - a number notation string
        返回:
        real number of s
        抛出:
        java.lang.Exception - deal with some exception when s disobeys scientific notation rules.
